00:18.018 --> 00:19.728
<i>Previously on </i> Bad Blood.

00:19.812 --> 00:22.232
They want us to move into fentanyl.
It's like heroin.

00:22.315 --> 00:24.942
- Where you gonna make it?
- You're standing in it.

00:25.025 --> 00:27.695
<i>Those twins,
they kidnapped my nephew.</i>

00:27.778 --> 00:29.405
I want Reggie back alive.

00:29.488 --> 00:32.033
I want 5 million from the drugs you stole.

00:32.116 --> 00:33.827
I have 30 seconds. You gotta help me.

00:33.910 --> 00:35.745
- My son's been kidnapped.
- What?

00:35.828 --> 00:37.288
This is not what I signed up for.

00:37.372 --> 00:41.083
What would you have done if someone
kidnapped your brothers, Bobby, Twix, Wes?

00:41.167 --> 00:44.503
You see what this animal is doing to us?
This is not what family does.

00:44.587 --> 00:47.298
I'm not putting this gun down
until you tell me where Reggie is.

00:47.382 --> 00:48.842
Do what you think is right.

00:48.925 --> 00:50.760
<i>Why aren't we going to the church?</i>

00:50.843 --> 00:53.680
Because those two Italian freaks
sent people there, Nats.

00:53.763 --> 00:55.140
You think I'm gonna forget this?

00:55.223 --> 00:58.058
<i>You should.
This was me and you fixing their mess.</i>

00:59.185 --> 01:01.645
<i>He had a gun on him.
They say that's intent.</i>

01:01.728 --> 01:03.732
They're charging him
with second-degree murder.

01:03.815 --> 01:06.818
You sent him alone to punish him.
It worked.

01:06.902 --> 01:08.737
<i>Is he in jail because of me?</i>

01:08.820 --> 01:11.197
Nats told me not to call the cops.
I should've listened.

01:12.115 --> 01:14.075
<i>My employer sent me to remind you</i>

01:14.158 --> 01:17.287
that our payment deadline
is still the same date.

01:17.370 --> 01:21.748
I'll be around just to make sure
that you stick to our agreement.

01:28.965 --> 01:31.758
<i>In this business,
no transaction would even happen</i>

01:31.843 --> 01:34.803
<i>without the imminent possibility
of it not happening.</i>

01:34.887 --> 01:36.472
♪ <i>Everything is the way it is</i> ♪

01:36.555 --> 01:38.683
<i>♪ It's got to be the way it is...</i> ♪

01:40.393 --> 01:43.688
<i>But there is a rush you get from it,</i>

01:43.772 --> 01:45.732
<i>and you either like it or you don't.</i>

01:46.732 --> 01:48.025
<i>I like it.</i>

01:48.108 --> 01:50.237
<i>♪ It's got to be like you say it is</i> ♪

01:56.075 --> 01:57.327
Yeah?

01:57.410 --> 01:59.328
<i>- Do you have our money?</i>
- I do.

01:59.412 --> 02:02.332
Good. I will send the container
and the crate numbers.

02:02.415 --> 02:04.833
Place them as instructed
before the ship leaves.

02:04.917 --> 02:07.212
What if someone finds it on the way?

02:07.295 --> 02:09.547
Don't worry.
We have people in the boat to keep watch.

02:09.630 --> 02:11.382
<i>- </i> Any other questions?
- No.

02:11.465 --> 02:15.803
Declan, I bet money on you.
Don't mess it up.

02:15.887 --> 02:18.515
<i>♪ It's got to be the way it is ♪</i>

02:55.468 --> 02:57.428
Well, ribs take a while to heal.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.972
Should I get an X-ray?

03:00.055 --> 03:01.765
No, they're probably cracked,

03:01.848 --> 03:03.977
and then there's nothing
you can do about that.

03:04.060 --> 03:05.437
Does it hurt anywhere else?

03:05.520 --> 03:08.940
Yeah, well, whole head, my face.

03:09.023 --> 03:11.858
Well, you are in good spirits,
considering.

03:11.943 --> 03:13.235
You're a good nurse.

03:14.237 --> 03:17.157
In this moment, everything's...

03:17.240 --> 03:18.950
...perfect.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.327
Hi, Reggie. Come on.

03:21.410 --> 03:23.453
I gotta do this thing.
I want you to come with me.

03:24.413 --> 03:25.873
He should probably rest.

03:25.957 --> 03:27.542
I don't want you out of my sight.

03:27.625 --> 03:30.378
- Where are we going?
- The port. Won't be long.

03:32.963 --> 03:35.300
- Maybe he should stay.
- No, no, no.

03:35.383 --> 03:37.385
The sea air will do me good.

03:37.468 --> 03:39.845
It's a river. It's full of piss and oil.

03:39.928 --> 03:42.973
Well, the last time you left me alone,

03:43.057 --> 03:44.392
things didn't go so good.

03:46.937 --> 03:49.105
So, yeah, I'm coming with you.

03:51.440 --> 03:54.068
Stay at my side. Stay quiet.

03:59.865 --> 04:02.868
<i>The hard work was done.
I had the cartel's payment.</i>

04:03.703 --> 04:05.383
<i>Now, it's not the way I planned to get it.</i>

04:05.413 --> 04:08.165
<i>But they don't care.
They just want their money.</i>

04:08.958 --> 04:10.125
<i>And in a few hours,</i>

04:10.208 --> 04:12.128
<i>the cash would be sailing
on the cargo ship</i>

04:12.212 --> 04:15.632
<i>and I would be right back
where I needed to be.</i>

04:23.097 --> 04:24.515
We all set?

04:24.598 --> 04:27.102
All good. Tape, locks.

04:28.268 --> 04:29.728
Yeah.

04:29.812 --> 04:31.605
Leave your car here. I'll walk you in.

04:40.823 --> 04:42.450
I've got an idea.

04:42.533 --> 04:44.618
I was thinking maybe
you could talk to Nats,

04:44.702 --> 04:47.497
you know, make a deal,
and he could tell you stuff.

04:47.580 --> 04:50.500
And then it'll be OK. We'll be OK.

04:50.583 --> 04:52.002
Whoa, what do you mean?

04:52.918 --> 04:54.212
We gotta get him out.

04:54.295 --> 04:56.130
He can't stay inside. That's ridiculous!

04:56.213 --> 04:59.050
I need him. I mean, he's my baby's father.

04:59.133 --> 05:00.258
I can't do it by myself.

05:00.343 --> 05:01.677
- OK.
- I need your help.

05:01.760 --> 05:03.595
- Val...
- I've been giving you my help.

05:03.680 --> 05:05.973
I've been helping you,
and you gotta help me.

05:06.057 --> 05:07.975
Nats killed an innocent civilian.

05:08.058 --> 05:09.935
- I'm telling you...
- I can't help with that!

05:10.018 --> 05:11.103
Listen, listen, listen!

05:11.187 --> 05:13.605
I'm saying, what if

05:13.690 --> 05:15.400
he tells you, you know,

05:15.483 --> 05:17.652
stuff about the family,
about the business?

05:17.735 --> 05:19.570
That'd be great, but even if he did,

05:19.653 --> 05:21.363
I can't cut a deal for his murder charge.

05:21.447 --> 05:23.742
You can! That's bullshit!
Yes, you can. There's a way.

05:23.825 --> 05:26.035
There's always a way. Have you see...

05:26.118 --> 05:28.287
Listen, you talk to a judge, something.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.205
I don't know! I want my husband back!

05:30.288 --> 05:32.875
Let's back it up. What do you have for me?

05:34.585 --> 05:36.212
What? What? What?

05:36.295 --> 05:37.963
Have you heard anything new?

05:38.047 --> 05:40.425
Maybe you overheard
Enzo or Domenic talking.

05:40.508 --> 05:43.093
Are you listening to me?
Are you listening to me?

05:43.177 --> 05:45.178
I'm not here

05:45.262 --> 05:47.765
to give you sweet nothing.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.100
You understand?

05:49.183 --> 05:51.310
It is your turn to give something to me.

05:51.393 --> 05:53.020
Nats doesn't deserve this.

05:53.103 --> 05:56.273
This, this monster kidnapped my son.

05:56.357 --> 05:58.025
He took my baby.

05:59.693 --> 06:02.405
Nats was being a father. I didn't help.

06:02.488 --> 06:04.573
You didn't help,
you didn't help, nobody helped.

06:04.657 --> 06:07.910
Nats was the only one who did something.

06:07.993 --> 06:09.995
He was trying to get this son of a bitch!

06:10.078 --> 06:12.038
Nats isn't in prison

06:12.123 --> 06:15.710
because of something you did
or I did or even Declan did.

06:15.793 --> 06:18.755
He's in prison
because this is what happens to criminals.

06:18.838 --> 06:20.673
No one's kidnapping
the kid of the librarian

06:20.757 --> 06:23.885
or the nurse who lives down the street,
just the kids of gangsters!

06:25.887 --> 06:27.430
I'm not telling you shit.

06:27.513 --> 06:29.265
OK, look,
I don't wanna go over this again.

06:29.348 --> 06:32.185
If Nats or Domenic find out
that you've been talking to me...

06:32.268 --> 06:34.020
You wouldn't dare.

06:34.103 --> 06:37.148
Just because Nats is on the inside
doesn't mean our relationship ends.

06:37.232 --> 06:40.735
Your information is what gives you worth,

06:40.818 --> 06:42.820
so get him to talk.

06:44.822 --> 06:46.990
We're done!

07:00.672 --> 07:02.548
What are we doing here?

07:02.632 --> 07:04.550
Gotta deliver this bag to someone.

07:05.968 --> 07:08.137
This will only take a few minutes,
in and out.

07:10.305 --> 07:11.682
Who's the money for?

07:11.765 --> 07:14.102
Reggie, let's just do this.

07:15.393 --> 07:17.605
It's not like I don't know what you do.

07:30.618 --> 07:33.203
Hey. There it is.

07:33.955 --> 07:36.623
Get those red-handle lock cutters.
This bag's going to Mexico.

07:36.707 --> 07:38.250
We're breaking into this thing?

07:38.333 --> 07:40.168
See this tape?

07:40.252 --> 07:42.172
Each one of these containers, Reggie,

07:42.255 --> 07:44.173
is checked by customs.

07:44.257 --> 07:46.175
They tape it up, lock it up,

07:46.258 --> 07:47.968
so that when it gets to where it's going,

07:48.052 --> 07:49.470
those people on the other side,

07:49.553 --> 07:51.472
they notice it hasn't been tampered with.

07:52.515 --> 07:55.685
Yeah, unless you got
more tape and more locks.

08:02.483 --> 08:03.985
277, this is the one.

08:04.068 --> 08:05.318
- Reg.
- Huh?

08:05.402 --> 08:07.028
Lift this with me. Come on, lift.

08:20.585 --> 08:21.793
Hey, guys. What's up?

08:21.877 --> 08:24.588
We've been tasked with a random search
of these here docks.

08:24.672 --> 08:26.882
You're kidding me!
No one told me about that.

08:26.965 --> 08:29.968
Hence the defining characteristic
of "random".

08:30.887 --> 08:33.972
I think I got this.
Money's going to Mexico.

08:34.057 --> 08:35.975
You must got a guy on the other side

08:36.058 --> 08:38.268
who'll get it before
customs even touches it, right?

08:38.352 --> 08:39.352
Right.

08:39.437 --> 08:40.938
But hiding it with baby stuff,

08:41.022 --> 08:43.648
that is the first place
that I would look for drugs or...

08:43.732 --> 08:45.400
Look at that one, DVD players.

08:45.483 --> 08:48.278
That's full of drugs.
Who buys DVD players anymore?

08:48.362 --> 08:49.447
I do!

08:55.410 --> 08:57.580
- Is that bad?
- Nah, it's alright.

09:00.792 --> 09:03.377
So, these containers
were just filled with merchandise.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.005
Why don't you come here
and lift stuff all the time?

09:07.088 --> 09:08.757
Because I'm not a thief,

09:08.840 --> 09:11.843
- and I'm done with baby seats.
- Right, of course.

09:12.928 --> 09:15.239
<i>I got a boat
that's leaving in three hours.</i>

09:15.263 --> 09:18.142
You know what kind of disaster
it'll be if it doesn't go out?

09:18.225 --> 09:20.560
No, I don't. We're gonna round up
everyone on these docks

09:20.645 --> 09:23.022
and cross-reference them
with the union list we got.

09:23.105 --> 09:25.065
Anyone not on that list,
we're bringing 'em in.

09:25.148 --> 09:27.693
Do you have any idea
how long that's gonna take?

09:27.777 --> 09:30.070
Long enough to get me to overtime.

09:30.153 --> 09:31.363
Let's go!

09:35.492 --> 09:36.785
Open it up.

09:41.373 --> 09:42.792
What are you doing?

09:42.875 --> 09:44.377
I got this new coffee maker.

09:44.460 --> 09:45.585
I'm trying to set the timer

09:45.670 --> 09:48.047
so that when I wake up,
the coffee's already made.

09:48.130 --> 09:50.609
- Make it when you wake up.
- I'd like it ready when I wake up.

09:50.633 --> 09:52.468
You can't wait five minutes for a coffee?

09:52.552 --> 09:55.095
I can, but I would rather not.
What's your problem?

09:55.178 --> 09:56.930
My son's in prison!

09:59.017 --> 10:00.183
Ah, I'm sorry.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.977
Oh, I can't sleep.

10:02.060 --> 10:04.813
What you're going through,
nobody should have to suffer.

10:04.897 --> 10:06.107
You want a hug?

10:06.190 --> 10:07.400
Kiss my ass!

10:07.483 --> 10:08.985
Come on.

10:09.068 --> 10:10.820
- Hey.
- It's gonna be OK.

10:10.903 --> 10:12.363
Sorry I'm late.

10:13.113 --> 10:14.240
Hey.

10:15.658 --> 10:18.160
- How's Nats?
- You know. You know.

10:19.412 --> 10:21.122
- Yeah.
- Hey.

10:21.205 --> 10:22.915
I'd offer you a coffee,

10:22.998 --> 10:24.875
except I have no idea
how this machine works.

10:24.958 --> 10:26.002
Sit down.

10:28.378 --> 10:30.715
We wanna talk to you
about the fentanyl business.

10:30.798 --> 10:32.425
Pa, you know what I think.

10:32.508 --> 10:34.218
I don't wanna deal with this right now.

10:34.302 --> 10:35.552
I feel the same.

10:35.635 --> 10:37.972
I can't be in the same room
as the two of them right now.

10:38.055 --> 10:39.973
But we gotta work with 'em.

10:40.808 --> 10:43.727
Now, I know you think
this is a good business opportunity,

10:43.810 --> 10:46.313
which is why I decided
you're gonna be the one in charge.

10:46.397 --> 10:48.982
I want you to get distribution
up and running.

10:49.067 --> 10:50.777
- Really?
- Yeah.

10:50.860 --> 10:52.362
Now, listen to me.

10:53.278 --> 10:55.613
You gotta be smart here, Luca.
You understand me?

10:55.698 --> 10:58.700
You gotta make sure these two
don't bring any trouble on this family.

10:58.783 --> 11:00.995
- And you tell us everything!
- Of course.

11:01.078 --> 11:03.080
I hate those two
for what they did to Nats.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.875
He's locked up cos of them.
But they want us to do this.

11:05.958 --> 11:07.877
I'm telling you,
it'll bring us a ton of money,

11:07.960 --> 11:09.712
and better we control from the start.

11:09.795 --> 11:13.507
Speaking of pineapples,
they wanna meet at the church.

11:13.590 --> 11:15.300
You call me right after.

11:15.383 --> 11:16.927
I got this.

11:17.010 --> 11:18.637
Yeah, thank you, Pa.

11:19.680 --> 11:22.223
Don't worry. You can trust me.

11:22.307 --> 11:23.392
Just be smart.

11:28.938 --> 11:30.607
Let's go for coffees.

11:31.608 --> 11:34.820
OK, but then I gotta get to church,
a real one.

11:36.072 --> 11:38.323
I'm putting in extra time.

11:38.407 --> 11:39.950
We need all the help we can get.

11:41.743 --> 11:43.162
Hang on, hang on.

11:44.705 --> 11:45.832
Yeah?

11:45.915 --> 11:47.851
<i>The cops are here doing a random search.</i>

11:47.875 --> 11:49.293
Well, shut it down!

11:49.960 --> 11:52.378
I can't.
I've never seen these guys before.

11:52.463 --> 11:53.463
I got no sway with them.

11:53.547 --> 11:55.340
<i>- So, what do we do?
- </i> Just don't move.

11:55.423 --> 11:58.343
<i>Stay on the boat.
I'll try to keep them off of it.</i>

11:58.427 --> 12:00.345
I'll call you when I know more.

12:01.555 --> 12:04.015
OK, we gotta pick it up.
Baby seat, let's go.

12:04.100 --> 12:05.977
- What's up?
- Let's go, let's go!

12:07.562 --> 12:09.272
Gotta move. Gotta clean this all up.

12:09.355 --> 12:11.523
Good, hand it to me. Good, good!

12:14.110 --> 12:17.905
Dissolve ENPP into pyridine and stir.

12:17.988 --> 12:20.448
At room temperature,
we add propionyl chloride...

12:21.533 --> 12:22.910
and stir for one hour.

12:22.993 --> 12:25.078
We pour that mixture into water,

12:25.162 --> 12:27.457
evaporate the solvent under vacuum until...

12:27.540 --> 12:29.583
Wait a second. Why am I watching all this?

12:29.667 --> 12:31.835
You should know everything
about your business.

12:31.918 --> 12:34.087
You think I'm gonna be making the drugs?

12:35.463 --> 12:37.173
What's so funny?

12:37.257 --> 12:39.050
The process of making fentanyl

12:39.135 --> 12:41.762
is highly complicated, very delicate.

12:41.845 --> 12:44.097
Right, yeah, so it would be ridiculous

12:44.182 --> 12:46.600
for someone like me
to even think about making this.

12:46.683 --> 12:47.768
Yes.

12:47.852 --> 12:49.645
Well, great!

12:49.728 --> 12:51.022
Can we go now?

12:51.105 --> 12:52.982
Cos this is boring me to death, really!

12:53.065 --> 12:55.108
Time management, folks!

12:55.943 --> 12:58.320
<i>Andiamo! </i> Time to go!

13:18.882 --> 13:20.425
If you're not serious about this,

13:20.508 --> 13:22.845
we can speak to Domenic
and find someone else.

13:22.928 --> 13:24.095
No, I'm serious.

13:26.557 --> 13:27.642
OK, Luca.

13:27.725 --> 13:29.643
So, it's your turn.

13:29.727 --> 13:31.603
- We want to know your plan.
- My plan?

13:32.855 --> 13:36.775
Unlike you, we like to know
everything about our businesses.

13:36.858 --> 13:39.237
So, tell us, how are you going to manage?

13:39.320 --> 13:42.173
Like I told you from the beginning,
you don't need to worry. I got it covered.

13:42.197 --> 13:43.990
OK. Well, show us.

13:46.577 --> 13:48.203
My distribution network?

13:48.287 --> 13:49.997
Exactly.

13:50.080 --> 13:51.873
We want to see how it all works.

13:53.542 --> 13:55.043
Up close.

13:55.793 --> 13:57.588
You want it, you got it.

13:59.548 --> 14:01.008
Let's go.

14:39.422 --> 14:41.090
Good. Let's go.

14:45.635 --> 14:48.347
Thank you.

14:54.227 --> 14:55.562
Put it on in the middle.

14:55.645 --> 14:57.355
Come on, let's move.

15:00.817 --> 15:02.862
Come on, this way. We gotta go this way.

15:02.945 --> 15:04.447
We're gonna lay low for a minute.

15:04.530 --> 15:06.532
We're gonna lay low.

15:16.958 --> 15:18.585
Hey, <i>bella!</i>

15:19.337 --> 15:21.088
How's the baby? Good?

15:21.172 --> 15:22.338
Good!

15:23.215 --> 15:24.925
Serena, <i>bella bambina!</i>

15:25.008 --> 15:27.343
Why are we here?

15:27.427 --> 15:28.887
What is he doing?

15:29.597 --> 15:33.350
I'll, uh, give you a call sometime, OK?

15:33.433 --> 15:35.435
See you guys later, OK?

15:37.437 --> 15:39.188
Why are we placing any of our business

15:39.272 --> 15:41.317
in the hands of this donkey?

15:41.400 --> 15:43.402
I think he'll surprise us.

15:43.485 --> 15:47.155
My sister, always the optimist.

15:48.782 --> 15:51.618
- Well?
- Well, what?

15:51.702 --> 15:53.245
That is your distribution empire?

15:53.828 --> 15:55.705
One of them.

15:55.788 --> 15:58.042
See the one in the black sweater?
That's Marie.

15:58.125 --> 16:00.918
She's my cousin,
which would make her your family too.

16:01.003 --> 16:03.463
Donna's also a cousin,
by marriage, though.

16:03.547 --> 16:05.048
Then there's Serena.

16:05.132 --> 16:07.425
I've known her since I was about 14.

16:07.508 --> 16:09.428
She took my virginity.

16:13.348 --> 16:16.560
A distribution empire
formed with family and prom dates.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.312
What could go wrong?

16:18.395 --> 16:19.772
And how exactly

16:19.855 --> 16:22.190
are you going to move
a kilo of drugs per week?

16:23.775 --> 16:25.360
Marie. There's a nurse.

16:26.153 --> 16:28.405
She's got a side business
going on worth 50K a week.

16:28.488 --> 16:31.158
Donna's a teacher.
Her husband works in a local college.

16:31.242 --> 16:33.743
Together, they run a string of dealers
in the schools.

16:33.827 --> 16:35.828
Serena's family runs an escort service

16:35.912 --> 16:38.123
out of a massage parlour down town, OK?

16:38.207 --> 16:41.168
All these ladies have been working with us
since they were 16 years old.

16:41.960 --> 16:45.255
They alone bring in 200 grand a month.

16:45.338 --> 16:47.967
While you two were going to
some fancy business school,

16:48.050 --> 16:50.468
I was working with my dad since I was 12.

16:50.552 --> 16:51.678
It's what I do.

16:53.138 --> 16:54.848
Luca, I can appreciate that.

